<title type="html"><![CDATA[I search for a nsf player with editable pitch table+nsf rec]]></title>

<content type="html" xml:base="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=8822&amp;p=92516#p92516"><![CDATA[
Tepples, if you want to adjust pitch in NSFPlay/NSFPlug you can actually just edit the CPU clock frequency in the in_yansf.ini file. This is probably the most robust way to transpose an NSF's pitch, and as you'd expect the update frequency will remain at 60hz or whatever it's set at in the NSF.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=5165">rainwarrior</a> — Sun Apr 15, 2012 8:04 am</p><hr />
]]></content>
