<title type="html"><![CDATA[I search for a nsf player with editable pitch table+nsf rec]]></title>

<content type="html" xml:base="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=8822&amp;p=92515#p92515"><![CDATA[
A nsf player can emulate any nes game regardless how different the nsf driver is. The nsf player pitch/frequency stream can be edited in real time by a pitch table module. Then record and save the new song that uses another scale. When recording a nsf. The frequencies of all notes is modified by the pitch table module. The new nsf song does not use the original nsf driver. It uses a new nsf driver. It's like importing nsf files in famitracker then connect only (Square 1) (Square 2) (Triangle) to pitch table. Then editing the pitch table. Then you have a new song. Then export it to nsf.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=5269">Jandazekon</a> — Sun Apr 15, 2012 7:59 am</p><hr />
]]></content>
